text: Gregory Matveieff (25 October 1901 - 15 August 1965) was a British diver. He competed in the men's 3 metre springboard event at the 1924 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1901 births Category:1965 deaths Category:British male divers Category:Olympic divers of Great Britain Category:Divers at the 1924 Summer Olympics Category:People from Westminster
